3) Store Module Scope (Java Backend – MVP + Future-Safe)

This document defines what the Store module is, what it includes in MVP (Mid plan), what is explicitly excluded, and how it is designed to evolve (variants later, without rewrite).

⸻

1) Purpose of the Store Module

The Store module is the commerce truth layer of the platform.

It owns:
	•	Products and categories
	•	Pricing
	•	Product images (Option A – Java owns images)
	•	Public catalog APIs (read-only)
	•	Merchant Admin CRUD APIs (write)
	•	Store-related permissions and plan gating

It does not own:
	•	Marketing pages (Payload)
	•	Checkout/payment execution logic (Payment module)
	•	Orders lifecycle (Order module – specified later)

⸻

2) Plan Scope (Locked)

2.1 Basic Plan
	•	❌ No store
	•	❌ No products
	•	❌ No catalog APIs
	•	✅ Website + content only

2.2 Mid Plan (Store MVP)

Includes everything in Basic, plus:
	•	✅ Product management (no variants)
	•	✅ Category management
	•	✅ Product images
	•	✅ Public catalog (read-only)
	•	✅ Cart eligibility (order creation later)
	•	✅ “Linked products” (pseudo-variants)
	•	✅ Better templates on the frontend

2.3 Pro Plan
	•	Includes Mid
	•	Adds scheduling, inventory, etc. (out of scope here)

