7) Product Images (Option A – Locked)

7.1 Ownership
	•	Images are owned by Java backend
	•	Stored in Cloudflare R2
	•	Metadata stored in DB

7.2 Image model
	•	Products can have multiple images
	•	One image can be marked as primary
	•	Images are ordered

This supports:
	•	Product galleries
	•	Listing thumbnails
	•	SEO alt text

⸻

8) Linked Products (Pseudo-Variants – Locked)

This is the MVP workaround for variants.

8.1 Concept
	•	Each option (color/size/etc.) is a separate product
	•	Products are grouped in a Variant Group
	•	Frontend renders them as selectable options
	•	Selecting an option navigates to another product page

8.2 Constraints (very important)
	•	All products in a group must:
	•	Belong to the same tenant
	•	Share the same primary category
	•	A product belongs to at most one variant group (MVP)
	•	Only one option dimension per group (Color OR Size)

8.3 Variant Group entity

Represents the “parent” concept.

Fields:
	•	id
	•	tenant_id
	•	name (e.g. “Coco Lipstick”)
	•	option_name (e.g. “Color”)
	•	timestamps

8.4 Variant Group Items

Links products into the group.

Fields:
	•	group_id
	•	product_id
	•	option_value (e.g. “Red”, “Nude”)
	•	sort_order
	•	is_default

8.5 Why this is safe
	•	No cart changes
	•	No inventory complexity
	•	No combinatorics
	•	Easy migration to real variants later

