9) Public Catalog APIs (Astro – Read Only)

The frontend (Astro + React islands) consumes Java APIs for catalog data.

9.1 Tenant resolution
	•	Tenant resolved by domain or slug before hitting Store APIs

9.2 Required endpoints (MVP)
	•	GET /public/{tenant}/catalog/categories
	•	GET /public/{tenant}/catalog/products
	•	GET /public/{tenant}/catalog/products/{slug}

Product detail response includes:
	•	Product core data
	•	Images
	•	Primary category
	•	Additional categories
	•	Linked products (variant group payload if present)

Payload CMS is not used for catalog truth.

⸻

10) Merchant Admin APIs (Write)

Merchant Admin is the only place to manage store data.

10.1 Required capabilities
	•	All Store actions require CAP_STORE
	•	Role enforcement:
	•	ADMIN & STAFF only

10.2 CRUD scope

Merchant Admin supports:
	•	Product create/edit/archive
	•	Category create/edit/archive/order
	•	Product images upload/reorder
	•	Variant group linking (pseudo-variants)

No bulk import/export in MVP (can be added later).

⸻

11) What Is Explicitly Out of Scope (MVP)

These are intentionally excluded:
	•	❌ Product variants (true variants)
	•	❌ Inventory reservations
	•	❌ Discount rules
	•	❌ Coupons
	•	❌ Shipping rules
	•	❌ Tax engines
	•	❌ Multi-currency
	•	❌ Product bundles

This keeps Mid MVP shippable and supportable.

⸻

12) Evolution Path (Important)

12.1 Adding real variants later

Planned, not blocked:
	•	Introduce product_variants
	•	Create default variant for each existing product
	•	Migrate cart to reference variantId
	•	Convert linked products into variants (optional)

12.2 Why current design supports this
	•	SKU already exists
	•	Price exists
	•	Images exist
	•	Categories exist
	•	Linked products already model “option groups”

No rewrite required, only migration.

⸻

13) Final Locked Decisions Summary
	•	Store is a separate module
	•	Mid plan includes store
	•	Products only (no variants)
	•	SKU auto-generated but editable
	•	Simple pricing
	•	Primary + additional categories
	•	Java owns product images
	•	Linked products used as pseudo-variants
	•	Astro consumes public catalog APIs
	•	Merchant Admin manages all store data

